The paper deals with complexity theory and circuit complexity, which are typically covered in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. The use of polynomial arithmetic and circuits also suggests the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The study of circuit depth and size falls under the cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) sub-category. The mention of fan-in and gates suggests the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. Finally, the use of lower bounds and optimality results suggests the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-category.
